The paper deals with the task of textual autocomplete, which is a natural language processing problem, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes an unsupervised approach that optimizes the efficiency-accuracy tradeoff, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the interpretability of the proposed approach, which is a topic of interest in the field of explainable AI, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the usability of the proposed approach in human-machine communication, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
